HEADWORD: Iodoquinine
<hw>I`o*do*qui"nine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Iodo-</ets> + <ets>quinine</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A iodide of quinine obtained as a brown substance,. It is the base
of herapathite. See <er>Herapathite</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

